CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 4, 1958, pg. A9., reads: "PITTSBURGH PIONEERS - The Pittsburgh Pioneers entertained their husbands at dinner, festive with he holiday spirit, at the home of member Helen Morrison on Broadhead St. Associate member Liylan [sic] Norris of Cleveland came over for the fun fest.  Seated, left to right: Mmes Mary Norman, Eleanor Jones, Muriel Bridges, Helen Morrison, Lulu Howell and Lilyan Norris.  Standing: Miriam Fountain, Agnes Stevenson, Lillian Brown, Elizabeth Henderson, Norine Cyrus, Marybelle Primas, Ruth Gonzales and Marian Bannister. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of fourteen women from Pittsburgh Pioneers Club, seated left to right: Mary Norman, Eleanor Jones, Muriel Bridges, Helen Morrison, Lulu Howell and Lilyan Norris; standing: Miriam Fountain, Agnes Stevenson, Lillian Brown, Elizabeth Henderson, Norine Cyrus, Marybelle Primas, Ruth Gonzales and Marian Bannister, gathered in Morrison home on Broadhead Street
